        <h3>1. Installation Issues</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> Unable to install the ContraVault Add-In from
          Microsoft AppSource.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Check Compatibility:</strong> Ensure your version of Microsoft
            Word supports Add-Ins from AppSource. ContraVault requires Word 2016
            or later, or a Microsoft 365 subscription.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Permissions:</strong> Ensure you have administrative rights to
            install Add-Ins in Word. If you’re on a company network, contact your
            IT administrator.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Restart Word:</strong> Close and restart Word, then try reinstalling
            the Add-In from AppSource.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2. Add-In Not Appearing After Installation</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> ContraVault is not visible in the Word ribbon
          after installation.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Enable the Add-In:</strong> Go to File > Options > Add-Ins. Under
            Manage, select COM Add-ins or Office Add-ins, and click Go. Check if
            ContraVault is listed and ensure it is enabled.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Check Disabled Add-Ins:</strong> If ContraVault appears under
            disabled Add-Ins, select it and click Enable.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Restart Word:</strong> Restart Word to refresh the Add-In ribbon
            display.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3. Slow or Unresponsive Performance</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> The ContraVault Add-In is running slowly or freezing.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Close Other Applications:</strong> High memory usage by other
            applications may slow down the Add-In’s performance. Close unnecessary
            programs.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Update Word:</strong> Make sure your Microsoft Word application
            is up to date. Go to File > Account > Update Options and select Update
            Now.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Clear Cache:</strong> Clear the cache in your Word Add-In settings.
            This can often resolve performance lags.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Reinstall the Add-In:</strong> Uninstall and reinstall the ContraVault
            Add-In from AppSource.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4. Unable to Access Certain Features</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> Specific features, like Clause Modification or
          AI Compliance Checks, are not working.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Check Your Plan:</strong> Ensure you’re subscribed to a plan
            that supports the feature you’re trying to access. Contact ContraVault
            support if you need help with upgrading your subscription.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Verify Internet Connection:</strong> Ensure you have a stable
            internet connection, as some features require cloud connectivity to work
            correctly.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Clear Cookies/Cache:</strong> Go to your browser settings and
            clear the cookies and cache used for Office Add-Ins.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Contact Support:</strong> If the issue persists, contact ContraVault
            support for further assistance.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5. Data Privacy or Security Concerns</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> Concerns about data being accessed by the Add-In.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Review Permissions:</strong> ContraVault only accesses the data
            in your active document. No additional data is collected without user
            consent.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Data Processing Security:</strong> All data processed by the
            Add-In is handled securely, in compliance with GDPR and other applicable
            regulations. For more details, refer to our Privacy Policy.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Contact Support:</strong> If you have further concerns, reach
            out to our privacy team or support.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>6. Error Messages or Crashes</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> Receiving error messages or the Add-In crashes
          unexpectedly.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Take Note of the Error Message:</strong> If an error message
            appears, take a screenshot or note the error code/message and contact
            ContraVault support.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Restart Word:</strong> Close all Word windows and restart the
            application.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Reinstall the Add-In:</strong> Uninstall the Add-In and reinstall
            it from Microsoft AppSource.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Run Office Repair:</strong> Go to Control Panel > Programs and
            Features > Microsoft Office > Change > Quick Repair. This can fix corrupted
            Office files affecting Add-In functionality.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7. Add-In Fails to Load</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Problem:</strong> ContraVault fails to load when opening Word.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Internet Connectivity:</strong> Check that you have a stable
            internet connection. Some features may require connectivity to load properly.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Check Firewall Settings:</strong> Ensure that your network/firewall
            settings allow access to ContraVault’s services. Contact your IT department
            if needed.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Clear Office Cache:</strong> In File > Options > Trust Center
            > Trust Center Settings, try clearing the Add-In cache.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Reinstall the Add-In:</strong> Uninstall and reinstall ContraVault
            from Microsoft AppSource.
          </li>
        </ul>

